author: blair
msg: Have 'svnadmin create' create start-commit.tmpl, pre-commit.tmpl and
post-commit.tmpl with the scripting code uncommented to make the
administrator's life easier.  Since the Subversion administrator
has to copy the template into the final location (minus the .tmpl
name), then presumably they will edit it.
Protect the expansion of the shell variables with "'s in case they
have embedded whitespace, such as a repository on Windows in some
odd directory.  And who writes shell scripts with ${VAR}???
